-- ── Cloudcraft ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Cloudcraft is a cloud architecture diagramming tool that automatically generates live, editable diagrams of AWS, Azure, Google Cloud, Oracle Cloud, and vSphere environments by reading a customer's live infrastructure data rather than requiring diagrams to be drawn entirely by hand. Founded in 2015, it was acquired by Datadog in November 2022 (not 2020) and now operates both as a standalone product at cloudcraft.co and as an integrated feature within the Datadog observability platform. It is headquartered in New York City.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium subscription with a free tier for individuals plus paid per-user Pro and Enterprise tiers, billed monthly or annually$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free plan available; Pro plan around $40.83/user/month billed annually ($99/month billed monthly)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2015, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$11-50 employees (operating as a Datadog product team)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$New York City, New York, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Cloudcraft Review: AWS Diagramming Pricing and Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Cloudcraft review: pricing, live AWS and Azure diagramming features, and how this Datadog-owned architecture tool works in 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Cloudcraft is a cloud infrastructure diagramming tool founded in 2015 and headquartered in New York City, built around the idea that architecture diagrams should stay automatically synchronized with a customer's real, live cloud infrastructure rather than becoming outdated the moment someone draws them by hand. Instead of manually placing shapes on a canvas, Cloudcraft can connect to a customer's cloud account and reverse-engineer a diagram of the actual deployed resources and their relationships, then keep that diagram updated automatically as the underlying infrastructure changes. Datadog, the New York-based observability and security monitoring company, acquired Cloudcraft in a deal announced on November 3, 2022; despite some sources loosely associating the acquisition with an earlier year, the transaction was confirmed by Datadog's own press release and investor materials as a November 2022 acquisition, and the deal terms were not disclosed. Since the acquisition, Cloudcraft has continued to operate as both a standalone product, available directly at cloudcraft.co with its own documentation, and as an integrated feature inside the broader Datadog platform, documented separately as Cloudcraft in Datadog, which combines live architecture visualization with Datadog's monitoring, security, and cost-management capabilities. Under Datadog's ownership, Cloudcraft's cloud coverage has expanded well beyond its original AWS-only focus to also support Microsoft Azure, Google Cloud Platform, Oracle Cloud Infrastructure, and VMware vSphere environments, letting teams visualize multi-cloud and hybrid infrastructure in one tool. The product renders diagrams in a distinctive isometric, 3D-style visual format rather than flat boxes-and-lines diagrams, which has been one of its recognizable design signatures since before the acquisition, and it supports drag-and-drop manual editing on top of the auto-generated baseline, along with cost estimation and budget-tracking overlays that show the estimated monthly cost of resources directly on the diagram. Cloudcraft's pricing follows a freemium model: a Free plan lets individual users create AWS and Azure architecture diagrams for both commercial and non-commercial projects at no cost, though live-sync and advanced features are typically reserved for paid tiers. The Pro plan is priced at roughly 40.83 dollars per user per month when billed annually, or 99 dollars per user per month when billed monthly, and includes a 14-day free trial that does not require a credit card, plus a 30-day money-back guarantee on top of that trial. An Enterprise plan is priced at roughly 100 dollars per user per month billed annually, or 120 dollars per user per month billed monthly, and adds enterprise-oriented capabilities such as expanded collaboration, administration, and support. As a small, focused product team of roughly a dozen to several dozen people operating within the larger Datadog organization, Cloudcraft's team size is modest, but customers benefit from the financial backing and platform integration of its much larger parent company. Cloudcraft is most commonly compared to other cloud diagramming and visualization tools such as Lucidchart, diagrams.net (draw.io), and native AWS architecture icon sets, but its core differentiator remains the live-data-driven, automatically generated diagram rather than a purely manual drawing canvas.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '469f4b55-236e-4e3e-b3d2-684fd59843f2';

